    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{9, 14, 5, 4, -20, -13, -5, 13\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{9 + 14 + 5 + 4 + (-20) + (-13) + (-5) + 13}{8}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{9 + 14 + 5 + 4 - 20 - 13 - 5 + 13}{8}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{20}{8} = 2.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n(9 - 2.5)^2 = 6.5^2 = 42.25\n$$\n$$\n(14 - 2.5)^2 = 11.5^2 = 132.25\n$$\n$$\n(5 - 2.5)^2 = 2.5^2 = 6.25\n$$\n$$\n(4 - 2.5)^2 = 1.5^2 = 2.25\n$$\n$$\n(-20 - 2.5)^2 = (-22.5)^2 = 506.25\n$$\n$$\n(-13 - 2.5)^2 = (-15.5)^2 = 240.25\n$$\n$$\n(-5 - 2.5)^2 = (-7.5)^2 = 56.25\n$$\n$$\n(13 - 2.5)^2 = 10.5^2 = 110.25\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n42.25 + 132.25 + 6.25 + 2.25 + 506.25 + 240.25 + 56.25 + 110.25 = 965.5\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $ n - 1 $ (sample variance formula)\n\n$$\ns^"
